// === IMPORTANT SECURITY DOCUMENTATION ===
//
// WHY we do NOT use string interpolation for shell commands:
//
//   VULNERABLE (DO NOT USE):
//     s"ls ${userInput}".!!
//     // If userInput = "; rm -rf /" → executes "ls ; rm -rf /"
//
//   SECURE (what we use):
//     Process(Seq("ls", userInput)).!!
//     // If userInput = "; rm -rf /" → passes it as a literal filename argument
//     // The OS treats it as a single argument, not as shell syntax
//
// Additional security layers:
//   1. Command whitelist — only pre-approved commands can run
//   2. Argument validation — reject shell metacharacters
//   3. Seq-based execution — no shell interpretation of arguments